               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300527-226-person1853">
                  JAMES 
                  COMFORT
               <interp inst="t18300527-226-person1853" type="surname" value="COMFORT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300527-226-person1853" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300527-226-person1853" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a butcher, and live with my father, in Farringdon-market. On the 30th of April the prisoner bought a piece of meat of me at my father's shop, it came to 20d. - she offered me half a crown; I took it to my next door neighbour, who said it was bad -Mr. Harrison took her in charge; she called herself Tomkins.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300527-226-person1854">
                  ANTONIO 
                  JULIAN WILLIAM HARRISON
               <interp inst="t18300527-226-person1854" type="surname" value="JULIAN WILLIAM HARRISON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300527-226-person1854" type="given" value="ANTONIO"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300527-226-person1854" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am clerk of Farringdon-market. The moment this half-crown was rung, I found it bad; I marked it, and sent for the beadle - I gave the half-crown and the prisoner to him.</p>

               <p>JAMES LLOYD. I received this half-crown from Harrison; the prisoner was searched, and a good half-crown was found on her; she gave the name of Tomkins.</p>
               <p>MR. FIELD. This is also counterfeit - they are both cast from Britannia metal.</p>
